{"id":"humiliation-of-christ","term":"Humiliation of Christ","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Philippians 2:8\">Phil. 2:8</a>), seen in (1) his birth (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Galatians 4:4\">Gal. 4:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 2:7\">Luke 2:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 1:46\">John 1:46</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 2:9\">Heb. 2:9</a>), (2) his circumstances, (3) his reputation (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 53\">Isa. 53</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 26:59\">Matt. 26:59</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 26:67\">67</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 22:6\">Ps. 22:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 26:68\">Matt. 26:68</a>), (4) his soul (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 22:1\">Ps. 22:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 4:1\">Matt. 4:1-11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 22:44\">Luke 22:44</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 2:17\">Heb. 2:17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:18\">18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 4:15\">4:15</a>), (5) his death (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 23\">Luke 23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 19\">John 19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Mark 15:24\">Mark 15:24</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Mark 15:25\">25</a>), (6) and his burial (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 53:9\">Isa. 53:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 27:57\">Matt. 27:57</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 27:58\">58</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 27:60\">60</a>).</p>\n<p>His humiliation was necessary (1) to execute the purpose of God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 2:23\">Acts 2:23</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 2:24\">24</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 40:6\">Ps. 40:6-8</a>), (2) fulfil the Old Testament types and prophecies, (3) satisfy the law in the room of the guilty (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 53\">Isa. 53</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 9:12\">Heb. 9:12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 9:15\">15</a>), procure for them eternal redemption, (4) and to show us an example.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Philippians 2:8","Galatians 4:4","Luke 2:7","John 1:46","Hebrews 2:9","Isaiah 53","Matthew 26:59","Matthew 26:67","Psalms 22:6","Matthew 26:68","Psalms 22:1","Matthew 4:1","Luke 22:44","Hebrews 2:17","Genesis 1:18","Genesis 4:15","Luke 23","John 19","Mark 15:24","Mark 15:25","Isaiah 53:9","Matthew 27:57","Matthew 27:58","Matthew 27:60","Acts 2:23","Acts 2:24","Psalms 40:6","Hebrews 9:12","Hebrews 9:15"]}